@pi Yeah I tried this before, I have two subdomains for my blog and I render the site with different configs… It was too ugly and soon became a mess.e.g. some content are externally managed:shrik3.com/misc/certs/gpg_full_pub.asc
and … alternative_theme.shrik3.com/misc/certs/gpg_full_pub.asc
It’s hard to manage the references across different subdomains i.e. themes. And at the end of the day your web server needs to point two domain names to different document root, but for externally managed stuffs it needs exceptions …
